<header class="post-header">

				<time class="post-date"><a href="https://www.ericzhang.me/gas-station-atgs-exposed-to-public/" title="Permalink to Gas Station ATGs Exposed to Public" rel="bookmark">January 29, 2015</a></time>
		
			<h1 class="post-title" data-text="Gas Station ATGs Exposed to Public"><a href="https://www.ericzhang.me/gas-station-atgs-exposed-to-public/" title="Permalink to Gas Station ATGs Exposed to Public" rel="bookmark">Gas Station ATGs Exposed to Public</a></h1>
	
	
</header><!-- /.post-header -->

<section class="article-content">

	<p>HD Moore from Rapid7 <a href="https://community.rapid7.com/community/infosec/blog/2015/01/22/the-internet-of-gas-station-tank-gauges" target="_blank">recently disclosed</a> that over 5800 Automated Tank Gauges at gas stations around the world were publicly accessible. Anyone connected to the internet can now view the in-tank inventories of the gas stations and manage the gas tanks.</p>
<p>The process to access the gauges is simple:<br />
1. Telnet into port 10001 of an ATG&#8217;s IP.<br />
2. Type ^A (Ctrl A) followed by I20100. This command outputs a basic report.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.ericzhang.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screen-Shot-2015-01-29-at-12.46.37-PM.png"><img src="https://www.ericzhang.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screen-Shot-2015-01-29-at-12.46.37-PM.png" alt="ATG telnet info" width="555" height="305" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-485" srcset="https://www.ericzhang.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screen-Shot-2015-01-29-at-12.46.37-PM.png 555w, https://www.ericzhang.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screen-Shot-2015-01-29-at-12.46.37-PM-300x165.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 555px) 100vw, 555px" /></a></p>
<p>There are over <strong>600 commands</strong> that can be executed, some of which include <strong>setting alarm thresholds, editing sensor configurations, and running tank tests</strong>. You can view them all in <a href="https://www.ericzhang.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/576013-635.pdf" target="_blank">the vendor manual</a>.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.ericzhang.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screen-Shot-2015-01-30-at-10.39.48-AM.png"><img src="https://www.ericzhang.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screen-Shot-2015-01-30-at-10.39.48-AM.png" alt="Commands" width="830" height="498" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-507" srcset="https://www.ericzhang.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screen-Shot-2015-01-30-at-10.39.48-AM.png 830w, https://www.ericzhang.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screen-Shot-2015-01-30-at-10.39.48-AM-300x180.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px" /></a></p>
<p>A list of affected IP&#8217;s can be found on <a href="https://www.shodan.io/search?query=port%3A10001" target="_blank">Shodan</a>.</p>

</section><!-- /.article-content -->
